sentences: Ivana Lang (15 November 1912 – 2 January 1982) was a Croatian composer, pianist and piano teacher.
She completed piano studies in 1937 at the Music Academy in Zagreb.
In 1937 Ivana acquired a degree in classical piano at the Zagreb Academy of Music.
Upon completion of studies at the Music Academy in 1937 she left her hometown of Zagreb in order to broaden and refine her study of composition with Joseph Marx at the Mozarteum in Salzburg.
